commit.message:
Assert compatibility with Django 1.10 and remove official Django<1.8 support

Refs #32

Fix up the `babel` command:

* Use `add_arguments` (`option_list` is old hat)
* Add tests

release version 0.5.1

* make imports absolute in babel templatetags
* strip quotes from translations via _()
* fix links in docs
* Add support for “trimmed” blocktrans content

Merge pull request #25 from robhudson/trimmed-support

Add support for "trimmed" blocktrans content

Merge pull request #26 from tsouvarev/strip-quotes-from-constants

Strip quotes from translations via _()

Merge pull request #31 from tsouvarev/fix-links-in-docs

Fix links in docs

Make imports absolute in 'babel' templatetags

This is needed because 'babel' file in templatetags named same as third-party package 'babel', so it confuses Python a bit
